body:
In python 2.X/3.X datetime module has it's own datetime.h file in standard (C headers) library. Fast creation of date/time/datetime instances require access to C API of datetime module. Addition of datetime.pxd could resolve this problem.

Given the immutable nature of date/time/datetime/timedelta objects by design we always have to recreate these objects when some of their properties have to change. So addition of inline functions for fast access to their members could help to do that as fast as possible.

commit.message: Add datetime.pxd to cython.cpython. Part II
Add new line at the end of file

Add function `import_datetime`

Add inline function `import_datetime` for initialization of PyDateTime C API.

title: Add datetime.pxd to cython.cpython
